articles.author: Eduardo Baptista, Hyunsu Yim, Joyce Lee
articles.description: Authorities were en route on Friday to execute an arrest warrant for impeached South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol, Yonhap News Agency reported, as a crowd of protesters faced off with police outside his residence and vowed to block any attempt.
articles.title: South Korea authorities moving to arrest impeached President Yoon, Yonhap says

articles.author: Brian Thevenot
articles.description: Investigators in New Orleans were searching for what motivated a U.S. Army veteran flying an ISIS flag from his truck to plow into a crowd of New Year's revelers, killing 15 people and injuring 30 more before dying in a shootout with police.
articles.title: Police probe motive in New Orleans truck rampage

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A gunman who killed at least 10 people in a rampage in a small town in Montenegro died from self-inflicted injuries on Thursday after attempting suicide, the country's interior minister, Danilo Saranovic, said.
articles.title: Suspect in Montenegro shooting dies after attempting suicide

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: An Israeli airstrike killed at least 10 Palestinians in a tent encampment sheltering displaced families in southern Gaza strip early on Thursday, medics said.
articles.title: Israeli airstrike kills at least 10 in southern Gaza, medics say

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Over 300,000 migrants crossed the Darien Gap into Panama in 2024, 42% fewer than the record number who made the perilous jungle crossing from South America a year earlier, Panama's migration authorities told Reuters on Thursday.
articles.title: Over 300,000 migrants crossed Latin America's Darien Gap in 2024, down 42%

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Bosnia's international peace envoy on Thursday sought to keep the country's European Union integration on track by rejecting the Serb Republic parliament's orders last week that would have blocked progress.
articles.title: Bosnia peace envoy declares Serb parliament's orders illegal

articles.author: Ronda Churchill, David Shepardson, Karen Brettell
articles.description: Gasoline canisters and large firework mortars were packed into the Cybertruck that burst into flames.
articles.title: FBI looks for any link between Tesla explosion and New Orleans attack

articles.author: Marc Frank
articles.description: In their New Year predictions, high priests from Cuba's Afro-Cuban Santeria religion told followers on Thursday to watch their health and spending, care for their families, guard against crime and drink less alcohol amid a punishing economic crisis entering its sixth year.
articles.title: Cuba's Santeria priests urge followers to hunker down amid crisis

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The Ukrainian military said it had carried out a high-precision strike on Thursday on a Russian command post in Maryino, in the Kursk region, where Ukrainian forces hold chunks of territory after a major incursion.
articles.title: Ukraine's military says it struck command post in Russia's Kursk region

articles.author: Hyunjoo Jin, Jihoon Lee
articles.description: Investigators to seize materials related to aircraft maintenance and operation of airport facilities.
articles.title: South Korea police search Jeju Air, airport operator over fatal plane crash
